Emaar Economic City (EMAAR) , a unit of
Dubaiâ€™s  Emaar Properties PJSC (EMAAR) , jumped the most in almost three
years after raising 5 billion riyals ($1.3 billion) from the
Saudi government to finance construction of real-estate projects
in the kingdom.  The shares climbed 9.5 percent, the biggest gain since Nov.
2008, to 8.10 riyals at the 3:30 p.m. close in Riyadh.  The 10-year loan from the Ministry of Finance will be used
to fund housing and business development near Jeddah through
2012. Loan repayment will start after three years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
